v 1
d hddid for Stata
d Based on Ning, Peng, and Tao (2024, Review of Economics and Statistics)
d Local package-browser/install entry; requires Stata 16+, lassopack, and multivariate x() needs hddid_clime.py + hddid_safe_probe.py with Python 3.7+, numpy>=1.20, and scipy>=1.7
d Install the Stata-side lasso dependency first with ssc install lassopack, replace
d For ancillary hddid_example.do use net install hddid, from("/path/to/hddid-stata") all replace or net get hddid, from("/path/to/hddid-stata")
d If Stata has not yet been bound to Python, first run set python_exec /path/to/python3
d After install rerun python query; confirm which hddid, which hddid_p, which hddid_estat, which hddid_dgp1, which hddid_dgp2, findfile _hddid_main.ado, findfile _hddid_display.ado, findfile _hddid_estimate.ado, findfile _hddid_prepare_fold_covinv.ado, findfile _hddid_pst_cmdroles.ado, findfile _hddid_mata.ado, findfile _hddid_p_current_surface.ado, findfile _hddid_preflight_current_vectors.ado, findfile hddid_safe_probe.py, findfile hddid_clime.py, which lasso2, which cvlasso, which cvlassologit, and which lassologit before the first paper-baseline call
d After that bundle check recover the installed walkthrough with findfile hddid_example.do and run do "`r(fn)'"
p hddid High-dimensional semiparametric DID estimator and DGP utilities
